{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/Linux/02-After-Install/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"87d017e1-abe0-56bd-acca-4e4a75d0ca39","html":"<h2>Setup your network</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      ping archlinux.org\n\npacman -S networkmanager network-manager-applet\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Enable NetworkManager service</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      systemctl start NetworkManager\n\nsystemctl enable NetworkManager\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Connect to Network</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      nmtui\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>Here we will simply add a new user to our system and give them wheel access</p>\n<h2>Add a user</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Add user</li>\n</ul>\n<code-fence lang=\"sh\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      useradd -m -g wheel <your_user>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<ul>\n<li>Create password</li>\n</ul>\n<code-fence lang=\"sh\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      passwd <your_user>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Switch users</h2>\n<p>To switch to your user run:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"sh\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      su <your_user>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Giving your user access to sudo</h2>\n<p>Make sure you have <code class=\"language-text\">vi</code> installed</p>\n<p>Enter:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"sh\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      visudo\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>and uncomment this line so it looks like this</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"sh\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      %wheel ALL=(ALL) ALL\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>if you hate typing your password everytime like me do this instead</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"sh\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      %wheel ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Need more?</h2>\n<p>check out man pages for the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>useradd</li>\n<li>userdel</li>\n<li>groupadd</li>\n<li>groupdel</li>\n</ul>\n<p>you can do this by typing:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      man <command>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Install Xorg</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      pacman -S xorg-server xorg-xinit\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Installing a DM</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      pacman -S lightdm\n\npacman -S lightdm-gtk-greeter\n\npacman -S lightdm-gtk-greeter-settings\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Enable lightdm service</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      systemctl enable lightdm\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>List our enabled services</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      systemctl list-unit-files --state=enabled\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Install i3wm (or any WM or DE)</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      pacman -S i3-gaps i3status i3lock dmenu\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>I'm using i3 but you can install any WM or DE you like best</p>\n<p>Here are some WM options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>dwm</li>\n<li>awesome</li>\n<li>bspwm</li>\n<li>xmonad</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here are some DE options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>XFCE</li>\n<li>KDE</li>\n<li>Gnome</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Install DE (Optional)</h3>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      pacman -S xfce4\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Install a terminal emulator</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      pacman -S alacritty\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>I'm using Alacritty but you can install any terminal emulator you want</p>\n<p>Here are some options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>st</li>\n<li>rxvt-unicode</li>\n<li>termite</li>\n<li>terminator</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Install a web browser and file manager</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      pacman -S firefox\n\npacman -S nautilus\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>We're done</h2>\n<p>You can now reboot into your new system!</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      reboot\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  ","excerpt":"Setup your network Enable NetworkManager service Connect to Network Here we will simply add a new user to our system and give them wheelâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"What to do after installing Arch Linux","tags":["archlinux"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/2f48c9e5fcafe362a0b8bfafe53c1518/a8734/arch-logo.png"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7747747747747749,"src":"/static/2f48c9e5fcafe362a0b8bfafe53c1518/5134e/arch-logo.png","srcSet":"/static/2f48c9e5fcafe362a0b8bfafe53c1518/06f82/arch-logo.png 197w,\n/static/2f48c9e5fcafe362a0b8bfafe53c1518/da7d7/arch-logo.png 393w,\n/static/2f48c9e5fcafe362a0b8bfafe53c1518/5134e/arch-logo.png 786w,\n/static/2f48c9e5fcafe362a0b8bfafe53c1518/7a32a/arch-logo.png 1179w,\n/static/2f48c9e5fcafe362a0b8bfafe53c1518/6c0d9/arch-logo.png 1572w,\n/static/2f48c9e5fcafe362a0b8bfafe53c1518/eeb1b/arch-logo.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Linux/02-After-Install/","prev":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Linux/03-AUR-yay/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Install packages from AUR with yay","tags":["archlinux"]}}},"next":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Neovim/13-sneak/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Sneak","tags":["neovim"]}}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}